<1ST_LINE>r i PM-BRF--Vietnam-China     05-19 0139</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>PM-BRF--Vietnam-China,0143</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Vietnam Frees 22 More Chinese Fishermen</HEAD>
<DATELINE>BANGKOK, Thailand (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Vietnam has freed 22 more Chinese
fishermen who were caught poaching in Vietnamese waters, the
official Radio Hanoi reported.
   The captives were turned over to Chinese officials on Wednesday
at Huu Nghi border post in the northern province of Lang Son
bordering China's Guangxi Province, according to a text of the
broadcast obtained in Bangkok today.
   On Monday, 68 Chinese fishermen were reportedly freed from the
central coastal province of Quang Nam-Danang.
   The releases follow repeated official Vietnamese requests that
Beijing free nine sailors captured during a brief clash in the
Spratlys islands in March and a pilot whose plane strayed across
the northern border into China last year.
   The clash in the South China Sea islands was over which country
had sovereignty over the chain.
