<1ST_LINE>r p PM-PoliticalQuotes     05-19 0175</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>PM-Political Quotes,150</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Quotes From the Presidential Campaign</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Here are some comments from the presidential
campaign trail:
</TEXT>
<TEXT>
   
   JESSE JACKSON, commenting Wednesday on the arrest of a St. Louis
couple charged with plotting to kill him: ``The climate for this
kind of antagonism and violence, of course, has been set by many
irresponsible public leaders (whose) attacks based on race have set
a divisive and dangerous climate, such as the one ... in New York
in April, for example.''
   
   GEORGE BUSH, declaring he won't negotiate with drug dealers:
``Drug dealers are domestic terrorists, killing kids and cops and
they should be treated as such. I won't bargain with terrorists and
I won't bargain with drug dealers either, whether they are on U.S.
or foreign soil.''
   
   MICHAEL DUKAKIS, on Jesse Jackson's claim that the ``super
delegate'' system has unfairly favored Dukakis: ``I think Jesse has
a perfect right to voice criticism of whatever he chooses to
criticize. I don't think we are going to have a fight with Mr.
Jackson.''
</TEXT>
