<2ND_LINE>PM-Taiwan-Crash,0122</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Military Training Plane Crashes In Taiwan, 5 Killed</HEAD>
<DATELINE>TAIPEI, Taiwan (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A military training plane slammed into a
house and exploded in a southern Taiwan town today, killing the
two-member crew and three people on the ground, police reported.
   Eight houses were set ablaze in the crash in Ah Lien Hsiang
town, 220 miles southeast of Taipei, local police said. The plane
was from Kanshan Air Base, six miles from the town.
   Two women and a 6-year-old girl who lived in the houses that
caught fire died in the accident, and three people were
hospitalized, police said.
   Police said they were uncertain what type of aircraft was
involved and have launched an investigation into the crash.
