<HEAD>Three Officers Plead Innocent To Supporting Coup</HEAD>
<DATELINE>MANILA, Philippines (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Three military officers pleaded
innocent today to charges of supporting an August 1987 coup attempt
that left 53 people dead and hundreds wounded.
   Also today, the military reported that seven people were killed
