<2ND_LINE>PM-Stroller Recall,140</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Umbrella Strollers Being Recalled</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Some 15,000 umbrella strollers with small
parts that may detach and pose a choking hazard are being recalled,
the Consumer Product Safety Commission announced today.
   The strollers were made by Services Merchandise Company of
Nashville, Tenn., and sold in Service Merchandise stores in 1986
and 1987, officials said.
   According to the commission, the strollers _ model 1601 PRT _
have 16 tube end plugs that can come lose and could then pose a
choking hazard for small children. No injuries have been reported.
   Service Merchandise is offering a free modification kit to
owners of the strollers who contact the firm at 1-800-251-1389.
Tennessee residents should call 1-800-251-1212. Requests can be
mailed to Service Merchandise Co., Customer relations Department,
P.O. Box 24600, Nashville, Tenn., 37202.
  
</TEXT>
