<2ND_LINE>AM-BRF--Classroom Stripper,0176</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Girls Surprise High School Teacher With Stripper</HEAD>
<DATELINE>KNOXVILLE, Tenn. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Mary Ruth Wilson was teaching her class
at West High School when a policeman showed up.
   She was surprised when he proceeded to handcuff her, and
resigned by the time he began to remove his clothes.
   The man was not a policeman, of course, but a stripper
apparently hired by the all-girl class for Ms. Wilson's birthday.
   ``I realized it was a joke when the girls started laughing,''
Ms. Wilson said, adding the man left on his shorts. ``They did it
because they liked me. The girls thoroughly enjoyed it.''
   Ms. Wilson said she was embarrassed and wishes the incident
earlier this month had not happened.
   ``He did not come through the office and had he, he would not
have been permitted,'' said Principal Charles Lowery. ``He was
trespassing.''
   The president of the Knox County PTA, Pam Guinn, said ``I'm
willing to bet that if some of the parents knew what happened, they
would be upset.''
