<HEAD>Parliament Approves Italian Space Agency</HEAD>
<DATELINE>ROME (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Parliament gave final approval Thursday to the
creation of an Italian space agency that will oversee domestic
satellite programs and coordinate projects with the European Space
Agency.
   The law, passed by both the Senate and the Chamber of Deputies,
allocates $1.8 billion over the next three years to the new agency,
Agenzia Spaziale Italiana (ASI), which will come under the
Scientific Research Ministry.
   Joint European projects include the Ariane 5 rocket and the
European space shuttle Hermes.
   On the domestic level the agency will deal mainly with
scientific and telecommunications satellites.
