<HEAD>Longtime AP Technician Leo Sadowski Dies</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NORRISTOWN, Pa. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Leo Sadowski, a technician for 42 years
at The Associated Press, has died of a heart attack. He was 63.
   Sadowski, who died Wednesday, joined The Associated Press in
1946 as a clerk and served in bureaus in Harrisburg, Pa., Trenton
and Newark, N.J.; New York, Boston and Philadelphia.
   During his career, he was promoted to wirephoto operator,
automatic operator, field maintenance technician, traffic
supervisor and traffic bureau chief.
   He is survived by his wife, Maria; a brother, Bernard, a 34-year
veteran of the AP working as a technician in Rahway, N.J.; and a
son and daughter.
