<HEAD>Production Goes Up This Week</HEAD>
<DATELINE>DETROIT (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Domestic automakers were scheduled to produce
256,931 cars and light trucks this week, up from last week's
252,408, Ward's Automotive Reports said Thursday.
   This week's production is higher than the same week a year ago,
in which 227,245 cars and light trucks were produced, the trade
journal said.
   U.S. automakers were scheduled to make 167,737 cars this week,
compared with 167,892 a week ago and 148,911 in the same week in
1987.
   Light truck production for the week was scheduled at 89,194,
compared with last week's 84,516 and last year's 78,334.
   Canadian automakers were to build 25,020 cars this week, down
from 27,168 a week ago and up from last year's 13,969.
   Canadian light truck production was scheduled at 18,760,
compared with 20,112 a week ago and 15,110 in the same week last
year.
</TEXT>
