<HEAD>U.S. Dollar, Stocks Higher In Early Tokyo Trading</HEAD>
<DATELINE>TOKYO (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The U.S. dollar opened slightly higher against the
Japanese yen in early trading Friday, while stock prices rebounded
following an overnight rally on Wall Street.
   The dollar opened at 124.85 yen, up from Thursday's close of
124.80 yen.
   ``The dollar has not moved very much since Tuesday's
announcement of the U.S. trade figures for March,'' said an
exchange dealer at a major commercial bank.
   According to figures released by the U.S. Department of
Commerce, the American trade deficit narrowed to $9.75 billion in
March from 13.83 billion dollars in February, the best monthly
performance in three years.
   On the Tokyo Stock Exchange, the Nikkei Stock Average of 225
selected issues, down a sharp 394.34 points Thursday, rose 117.71
points to 27,490.95 in the first 15 minutes of trading.
   The decline on Thursday had been the key market index's biggest
single-day loss this year.
